# Initializing image counter in a dictionary
imageCounter = {} #creating dictionary for image counts

# creating a function to count images in a directory
def birdImageCounter(dir_path):
    lab10Bird = os.scandir(dir_path)
    lab10birdImages = 0
    for path in lab10Bird:
        if path.is_file():
            lab10birdImages += 1
    return lab10birdImages
In[]:
# creating function to count number of images in each sub-directory within a directory
def birdImagesCounterSubDir(sub_dir_path):
    for birdSubDir in os.scandir(sub_dir_path):
        if birdSubDir.is_dir():
            birdsDir = birdSubDir
            imageCounter[birdsDir] = birdImageCounter(birdSubDir.path)

# Specify the path to your 'birds' folder
source = pathlib.Path('/Users/samiksharajpal/Desktop/archive')

# Specify the new path where you want to copy the selected classes
newSource = pathlib.Path('/Users/samiksharajpal/Desktop/archive/newBirds')

# Create new subfolders in the new structure
for subfolder in ['train', 'test', 'valid']:
    new_subfolder_path = newSource / subfolder
    new_subfolder_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)

# Loop through each subfolder
for subfolder in ['train', 'test', 'valid']:
    subfolder_path = source / subfolder
    
    # Loop through selected classes
    for selected_class in birdsTop3class:
        class_name = selected_class
        
        # Check if the class folder exists
        class_folder_path = subfolder_path / class_name
        if class_folder_path.exists():
            # Create a new folder in the new path
            new_class_folder_path = newSource / subfolder / class_name
            new_class_folder_path.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)
            
            # Copy all files from the original class folder to the new folder
            for file_name in os.listdir(class_folder_path):
                file_path = class_folder_path / file_name
                shutil.copy(file_path, new_class_folder_path)

# Print a message indicating that the copy is complete
print(f"Selected classes copied to {newSource}")

Data Augmentation

In[]:
augmented_data = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=20,
    shear_range=0.2,
    zoom_range=0.2,
    horizontal_flip = True,
    fill_mode = 'nearest'
)

test_datagen = ImageDataGenerator()

train_generator = augmented_data.flow_from_directory(
    train_path,
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='categorical',
)

validation_generator = augmented_data.flow_from_directory(
    valid_path,
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='categorical',
)


test_generator = test_datagen.flow_from_directory(
    test_path,
    target_size=(224,224),
    batch_size=32,
    class_mode='categorical',
)

  1. Defining a Full Model
In[]:
inputs = keras.Input(shape=(224, 224, 3))
x = keras.applications.vgg16.preprocess_input(inputs)
x = conv_base(x)
x = layers.Flatten()(x)
x = layers.Dense(128)(x)
outputs = layers.Dense(3, activation="softmax")(x)
model = keras.Model(inputs, outputs)

Evaluate the model

In[]:
def model_eval(model,test_data):
    # Make predictions
    predictions = model.predict(test_data) 
    # Convert predictions to class labels
    y_pred = np.argmax(predictions, axis=1)
    # True labels
    y_test = test_generator.classes
    
    eval = {}
    eval['Accuracy'] = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)*100
    eval['Precision'] = precision_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted')*100
    eval['Recall'] = recall_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted')*100
    eval['f1 score'] = f1_score(y_test, y_pred, average='weighted')*100
    for k,v in eval.items():
        print(f"{k}\t{v:.2f}")
    return y_test,y_pred

from keras.utils import to_categorical
# prediction labels
pred = model.predict(test_generator)

# True labels
true = test_generator.classes
true = to_categorical(true)
for i in range(3):
    actual = true[:, i]
    predictions = pred[:, i]
    precision, recall, _ = precision_recall_curve(actual, predictions)
    label = f"[{img_labels[i]}] AUC = {auc(recall, precision):.2f}"
    plt.plot(recall,precision,lw=2,label=label)

In[]:
misclassifiedIndices = np.where(y_pred != y_test)[0]

plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
for idx,i in enumerate(misclassifiedIndices):
    
    # doing calculations to find the image in the test_generator 
    batchIndex = i // test_generator.batch_size
    batch, _ = test_generator[batchIndex]
    imageIndexInsideBatch = i % test_generator.batch_size
    img = batch[imageIndexInsideBatch] #misclassification image

    
    actualLabel = img_labels[y_test[i]]
    predictedLabel = img_labels[y_pred[i]]

    plt.subplot(4, 5, idx + 1)
    plt.imshow(img.astype("uint8"))
    plt.title(f"Actual: {actualLabel}\n Predicted: {predictedLabel}",fontsize=8)
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.1, hspace=0.1)
plt.show()

Conclusion: The model although performed okay for train and validation set but is performing super low for test data; seems the data is not sufficient for model to learn properly
